{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"C\n    \n      Context Object in Core — Client Injects, Core Guides\n      PiqleyCore provides RuleEditingContext — the client injects available fields, installed plugins, and existing rules. Core then exposes what's possible given that context: valid fields to match, valid patterns for a field, valid actions for an emit/write. The CLI queries the context at each wizard step.\n      \n        \n          Pros\n          \n            Core is the single source of truth for \"what's valid here\"\n            Clients stay thin — just render choices Core provides\n            Field discovery logic injected, not owned by Core\n            GUI gets the same context-aware validation for free\n          \n        \n        \n          Cons\n          \n            Most upfront design work\n            Context object must model the full editing domain","choice":"c","id":null,"timestamp":1773941232396}
